   "source": [
    "## What the Sunburst Plot Shows:\n",
    "\n",
    "### Hierarchy Levels:\n",
    "The plot is divided into four levels:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Region**: The outermost level, showing different regions.\n",
    "2. **Category**: Nested within each region, showing different product categories. \n",
    "3. **Sub-Category**: Further nested within each category, showing different sub-categories of products.\n",
    "4. **Metric**: The innermost level, showing three metrics: Sales, Discount, and Profit.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Segment Size:\n",
    "The size of each segment corresponds to the aggregated Value (sum of sales and profit, and mean of discount) for that particular combination of Region, Category, Sub-Category, and Metric.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Color Scale:\n",
    "The color of each segment represents its Value, with a continuous color scale (RdBu) used to differentiate values visually."
   ]
